<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Configure SOCKS Proxy</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Enable and maintain SSH connection on MacOS</h1>
<ul>
    <li>From your terminal, type the following command:</li>
</ul>
<code><div id="contentToCopy0">ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -f -N -M -S /tmp/sshtunnel -D 1080 ubuntu@${ip_gw} -p22</div>
<br>
</code><button id="copyButton0">Copy</button>
<ul>
    <li>Keep that terminal open to keep the proxy open. Closing it will kill the proxy</li>
</ul>
<h1>Enable and maintain SSH connection in Windows using CMD</h1>
<ul>
    <li>From your terminal, type the following command:</li>
</ul>
<code><div id="contentToCopy1">ssh -D 1080 -C -N -o ServerAliveInterval=60 -o ServerAliveCountMax=3 ubuntu@${ip_gw}</div>
    <br>
</code><button id="copyButton1">Copy</button>
<ul>
    <li>Keep that cmd tab / window open to keep the proxy open. Close the tab or window to close the proxy</li>
</ul>
<h1>Enable and maintain SSH connection on Windows using Putty</h1>
<ul>
    <li>Download and Install Putty if you don't have it</li>
    <li>Open Putty and configurea a new session</li>
    <li>Enter the remote gw-vcf IP: ${ip_gw}</li>
    <li>Save a new session using the name: GW_VCF</li>
    <img src="putty-gw-vcf-1.png" width="792" height="304" alt="putty-gw-vcf-1.png">
    <li>Click on Data under Connection</li>
    <li>Enter the Auto-login username: ubuntu</li>
    <img src="putty-gw-vcf-username.png" width="792" height="304" alt="putty-gw-vcf-username.png">
    <li>Add the proxy tunnel config:</li>
    <ul>
      <li>Expand the SSH folder and click on Tunnels</li>
      <li>Click the Dynamic button (critical)</li>
      <li>Enter 1080 in the Source port under Add new forwarded port:</li>
    </ul>
    <li>Click ADD</li>
    <img src="putty-gw-vcf-socks_tunnel_add.png" width="792" height="304" alt="putty-gw-vcf-socks_tunnel_add.png">
    <li>Verify the forwarded port was added correctly: Should see D1080:</li>
    <img src="putty-gw-vcf-socks_tunnel_configured.png" width="792" height="304" alt="putty-gw-vcf-socks_tunnel_configured.png">
    <li>Go back to the Session and make sure you SAVE the recent changes to the GW_VCF session</li>
    <li>Now you can establish the proxy connection by Opening the session</li>
    <li>You will be prompted for a password</li>
    <li>Use the Firefox browser configured per the FireFox section when the putty session is open</li>
    <li>To clos the session, close the putty session window</li>
</ul>
<h1>Create Windows Shortcut auto login with cmd line argument and password:</h1>
<ul>
    <li>Important to use the same session name saved previously: GW_VCF</li>
    <li>Right click on your Windows desktop > Create New Shortcut</li>
    <li>Enter this command in the target: (replaces the password field)</li>
    <li>Shortcut Target:  "C:\Program Files\PuTTY\putty.exe" -load "GW_VCF" -pw "enter password here between the quotes"</li>
    <li>Save the shortcut: Click Apply and OK</li>
    <li>Now when you run the shortcut, it auto login and starts the proxy. You can save ths shortcut to your Windows Taskbar</li>
    <img src="putty-gw-vcf-shortcut.png" width="792" height="304" alt="putty-gw-vcf-shortcut.png">
</ul>
<h1>Configure Firefox</h1>
<img src="socks1.png" width="792" height="304" alt="Firefox settings">
<br>
<img src="socks2.png" width="450" height="506" alt="Firefox Proxy settings">
</body>
</html>
<script>
function setupCopyButton(buttonId, contentId) {
    const copyButton = document.getElementById(buttonId);
    const contentToCopy = document.getElementById(contentId);

    if (copyButton && contentToCopy) {
        copyButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
            const textToCopy = contentToCopy.innerText;

            navigator.clipboard.writeText(textToCopy)
                .then(() => {
                    // alert(`Content for ${contentId} copied successfully!`);
                    console.log(`Content from ${contentId} successfully copied.`);
                })
                .catch(err => {
                    console.error('Could not copy text: ', err);
                    alert('Failed to copy content. Please try again.');
                });
        });
    } else {
        // Log errors if the elements are missing in the HTML
        if (!copyButton) {
            console.error(`Copy Button with ID '${buttonId}' was not found.`);
        }
        if (!contentToCopy) {
            console.error(`Content Element with ID '${contentId}' was not found.`);
        }
    }
}

// ====================================================================
// MAIN EXECUTION BLOCK (Runs ONLY when the page is fully loaded)
// ====================================================================

